{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNMultiPoint","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"}],"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineOnUserTap","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can add polyline shapes to the map by adding them to an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object. Configure the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"text":"’s or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"text":"’s polylines collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"text":" object. To access a polyline’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polyline overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:"},{"text":" methods. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polyline overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:lineWidthForPolylineAnnotation:"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them. The first and last vertices are not connected to each other, but you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specify the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the first and last vertices in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"order to close the polyline. To fill the space within the shape, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"text":" object. To group multiple polylines together in one shape, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollection"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To make the polyline go across the antimeridian or international date line,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specify some longitudes less than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a polyline that stretches from Tokyo to San Francisco would have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinates of (35.68476, -220.24257) and (37.78428, -122.41310).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let coordinates = [","    CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 35.68476, longitude: -220.24257),","    CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.78428, longitude: -122.41310)","]","let polyline = MLNPolyline(coordinates: coordinates, count: UInt(coordinates.count))"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A polyline is known as a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"LineString","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geometry in GeoJSON.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"Related-examples","text":"Related examples","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineOnUserTap"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"mino